  "abstract": "\u003cjats:p\u003eWe compared two joint likelihood approaches, with complete (L1) or without (L2) linkage disequilibrium, under different ascertainment schemes, for the genetic analysis of the disease trait and marker gene 1 in replicate 42. Joint likelihoods were computed without a correction for the selection scheme. For the different sampling schemes we have explored, our results suggest that L1 is a more powerful approach than L2 to detect major gene and covariatc effects as well as to identify accurately gene×covariate interaction effects in a common and complex disease such as the Genetic Analysis Workshop 12 MG6 simulated trait. © 2001 Wiley‐Liss, Inc.\u003c/jats:p\u003e",
